name: Vintage Radio Screen Print - Super Admiral
description:
• 3 color screen print
  • Very limited edition of 15, signed and numbered
  • Printed on 12x12" bristol paper
*** These were all individually crafted; no two are alike, each with their own endearing imperfections.

*** Colors on actual print may vary from photo due to everyone having a different monitor, and unique calibration settings

name: Polaroid SX-70 Print
description:
• 2 color screenprint
  • Individually hand pulled, with each its own uniquely endearing characteristics
  • Printed on super heavyweight card stock– on French Paper's Muscletone, slightly off-white with a muted cool green hue
  • 8.5 x 11"
  • Limited edition of 22, each signed and numbered, with love!
  • Black ink surface shows subtle flecks of metallic, a small amount of silver paint was combined with plain black for a more interesting effect.
Please go here to read Wikipedia’s page on the Polaroid SX-70 for more information about this gorgeous, iconic camera.

name: Gopher
description:
He's not sad... he's just serious!
  • 4 Color Gocco Print
  • Limited Editon

name: Octossert
description:
Sure, he looks pissed. But you'd be angry too if you got mistaken for a scoop of ice cream. The bandage? The little ice cream lever thingy nicked him on his way out.

Octossert was printed on medium weight cream-colored cardstock, at 5x7" using a Vandercook letterpress. There are two options for him, black or in full color.

There are only 10 prints of single-color black, so get them before they run out!
